--- CRITICAL BUG 1: Wrong CIK lookup URL ---
File: app/services/edgar_client.py, line 86
Code:  url = f"{EDGAR_DATA_URL}/files/company_tickers.json"
       → https://data.sec.gov/files/company_tickers.json → 404 NOT FOUND

Correct URL: https://www.sec.gov/files/company_tickers.json → 200 OK
Verified: www.sec.gov returns AAPL with CIK 320193

Impact: _resolve_cik() ALWAYS returns None for every ticker.
- get_insider_transactions('AAPL') → returns empty list []
- get_major_position_changes('AAPL') → returns empty list []
AAPL (Apple Inc.) definitely has Form 4 insider transactions and 13D/13G filings.
These methods are completely non-functional.

Violates:
- AC4: "Form 4: get_insider_transactions(symbol, limit=20) — fetches recent Form 4 filings"
- AC8: "13D/13G: get_major_position_changes(symbol, limit=10) — fetches recent 13D/13G filings"
- AC11-12: Form 4 field requirements (no data returned at all)
- AC9: 13D/13G field requirements (no data returned at all)

--- CRITICAL BUG 2: 13F holders always return null shares_held and value ---
File: app/services/edgar_client.py, lines 142-148
The EFTS search-index only returns filing metadata, not actual holdings data.
Code hardcodes: shares_held=None, value=None, change_type="held" for every entry.

Sample output (all 20 entries for AAPL):
  {"institution_name": "Wellesley Investment Advisors (CIK 0001533551)",
   "shares_held": null, "value": null, "report_date": "2014-03-25", "change_type": "held"}
Every single entry has null shares and null value. Report dates range from 2002-2023
(not recent/latest). These are random filers, NOT top institutional holders of AAPL.

Violates:
- AC5: "Each holder includes: institution_name, shares_held, value, report_date, change_type"
  (shares_held and value are always null)
- AC4: "13F: get_institutional_holders(symbol, limit=20) — fetches latest 13F filings"
  (data is from random years, not latest)

